The paper deals with sparse recovery problems using random matrices, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of model-based sparsity also suggests a connection to optimization and combinatorial algorithms (cs.DS). The mention of restricted isometry property and probabilistic methods suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the robustness analysis suggests a connection to signal processing (cs.SI).
